		<h3>Covid-19 Information<br>
</h3>
		
		
		
		
		
			<p class="summary">S&amp;S CISD COVID-19 Updates</p>
		
		
		
			<span class="text rteSpan"><p class="MsoNoSpacing"><strong><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>4-3-2020</span></strong><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'><p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>S&amp;S CISD
Families,<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>On March 31<sup>st</sup>
Governor Greg Abbott announced he was extending the closure of schools through
Friday May 1<sup>st</sup>. The earliest we could return to school is Monday,
May 4<sup>th</sup>. Please understand assessing the Covid-19 (coronavirus) pandemic
is an ongoing situation and these dates could once again be changed at the
state or local level if needed.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>We have spent
the last two weeks getting feedback from everyone as we determined how to best
move forward with a combination of low tech and high tech delivery of
instruction in a distant learning environment. Please see some of the changes
we are implementing this week as we anticipated an extended school closure.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>        
</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Teachers
will have weekly lessons prepared each Friday to cover the following week. For
example, the assignments going out on Friday, April 2<sup>nd</sup> will be
labeled WEEK OF APRIL 4<sup>th</sup>.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>        
</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>The
majority of assignments will be delivered electronically but students in grades
Pre-K, Kindergarten, and 1<sup>st</sup> grade will receive a physical packet
instead. Students without access to the internet will also receive a physical
packet. We have been able to provide a technology device to households
currently without one. Providing internet/wifi has been a bigger challenge so
if you are unable to connect and require a physical packet please contact the
campus principal directly or send an e-mail to info@sscisd.net<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>        
</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>For
those receiving a physical student packet they will be available for drive
through pick up each Saturday morning from 9AM to 11AM at the elementary and
middle school campuses. <p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>        
</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>For
those unable to pick them up we will either hand deliver or mail on Monday
morning depending on location.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>        
</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>We
encourage the use of electronic submissions (taking a picture of assignment to
be graded and sending an e-mail directly to the teacher). We will also have a
drop off box for grades Pre K through 12 located just inside the front doors at
the elementary in Southmayd as well as the middle school in Sadler. These
locations will be unlocked and available only on Thursdays from 8-4 and Fridays
from 8-5.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Thank you for
working together with all of us during this time away from the traditional
school setting that we have come to miss so very much. Please take care of
yourself and your family. <p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Roger Reed<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">



































</p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Superintendent<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong></strong><br></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong></strong><br></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>​​​​​​​</strong><strong>3/20/2020</strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong></strong><span style='font-size: 11pt; font-family: "Comic Sans MS";'>Campuses are closed through April 3<sup>rd</sup>
due to the Covid-19 (coronavirus). If you need assistance during this time,
please contact the administration office at 903 564-6051 ext 4001. Please refer
to the school website at </span><a target="_blank" href="http://www.sscisd.net/"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>www.sscisd.net</span></a><span style='font-size: 11pt; font-family: "Comic Sans MS";'> for additional
information including:</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:auto;
text-indent:-.25in;mso-outline-level:1;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>       </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Distance Learning <p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:
auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-outline-level:1;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>       </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Teacher E-mail addresses<p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:auto;
text-indent:-.25in;mso-outline-level:1;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol">·<span style='font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>       </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Current School Closure
Information<p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>We have set up a general e-mail address </span><a href="mailto:info@sscisd.net"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>info@sscisd.net</span></a><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> for all general questions.
Use this e-mail if you have questions or need something but are not sure who to
direct it to.</span><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"> <p></p></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Thank you for
your understanding as we work together to prevent the spread of this global
pandemic.<p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'>As we
enter our 2<sup>nd</sup> full week of the Covid-19 school closure we plan to
continue our “grab and go” breakfast and lunch distribution with a couple of
small modifications. Our plan is to pass out multiple meals that will include
lunches and breakfasts each Monday and Thursday from 11:00 AM to 12:00 PM at
the elementary (located at student drop off area) and the middle school
(located at student drop off area). These meals are available to all S&amp;S
Pre-k through 12<sup>th</sup> grade students free of charge. Meals can be
picked up at either location regardless of the campus your child attends.
Please stay in your vehicle and the meals will be brought out to you in a quick
and safe manner. <p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'>Meals
may be picked up for students living near you (for those without
transportation) by simply providing the student or students’ names. <p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'>If you
are in need of meals but find yourself unable to access them please contact the
administration office at 903 564-6051 or send an e-mail to </span><a href="mailto:info@sscisd.net"><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Comic Sans MS";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;
color:#0563C1'>info@sscisd.net</span></a><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Comic Sans MS";mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:
minor-bidi'> and we will find a way to help.<p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>Thank you.<p></p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'> </span></p>

<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style='font-family:"Comic Sans MS"'>S&amp;S CISD<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><br></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><br></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><br><span style='font-family: "Comic Sans MS";'></span></p>
